# c/MessageSystem

ApproxDuration: ""
DependsOn: "c/Entity"

# Description
enum MessageType;
class Message { virtual MessageType getType() = 0 };
class MessageBox { list<Message*> };
Entity { MessageBox };

Every <Sub>Message-class has a unique MessageType, which is returned in <Sub>Message::getType().
The Entity can push new Messages into his own MessageBox.
The "game" can poll these Messages.
Every Message has a field in which it can define, when to poll it.

